		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>wow, to the origional poster of this thread, I tip my hat to you.&nbsp; you really seem to understand exactly what made pvp the best thing to ever happen to this game.&nbsp; You also understand why the game is no longer what it was for alot of old players.&nbsp; The thrill of pvp is misunderstood, or all together unknown to most it seems.&nbsp; The risk, intensity, reward of winning a good fight are much better than killing an AI monster.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would like to adress Item loot, which is a touchy subject.&nbsp;&nbsp; item loot crreates a pvp enviroment where one must always be ready, and willing to die.&nbsp; However, playing on rallos zek, I have noticed that this has created untrusting people.&nbsp; People are afraid you will backstab them, and take a good piece oif their gear.&nbsp; My short tenure on rallos zek led me to the conclusion that most of its inhabitents HATED pvp, and wanted nothing to do with it.&nbsp; The server is literally 99% blue, as most folks who pvp are shunned as PKERS.&nbsp;&nbsp; again, its a tough subject to consider:&nbsp; does item loot help or hurt the overall EQ pvp cause?&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another big problem with pvp servers are the number of folks who do not want anything to do with pvp ( as mentioned with item loot).&nbsp; As a pvp druid on vallon zek for years ( dimitrakos), I killed many people , and those people usually send tells which were offensive in nature.&nbsp; Most of them wanted nothing to do with pvp, especially the people who were set on leveling.&nbsp; My reply to them was " why did you make a char on a pvp server" to which most of them replied " F*** you".&nbsp;&nbsp; My overall point is, a server with pvp in mind will work only if the people who inhabit it are playing to pvp, not pve all day and night.&nbsp; Obviously this is idealized</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
