	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=23342'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#33CC00;font-weight:bold; '>Rytan_the_Wyrmlord</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			EQ Designer<br>
			
				Posts: 312<br>
				
				Registered: 04-07-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=23342'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=800#M800">81</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 696 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P><SPAN **Potty Mouth**"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">I don't think item loot and exp loss on death would be well received for the most part.&nbsp; People are too attached to their items and levels.&nbsp; Right now the point system is set up so that you lose points when you die.&nbsp; Currently it's 1/4, but it's being upped to 3/4.&nbsp; You obviously can't have them losing exactly the same as gaining because you'd end up with no points eventually.<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>ffice<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>ffice" /></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN **Potty Mouth**"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">The old school Zek in me would like to see a original release server as well, but I don't think it would have long term draw.&nbsp; Eventually you'd have to allow the expansions to keep people interested and motivated to improve.&nbsp; Otherwise it's pointless to even have levels.&nbsp; You might as well start everyone at max level and go from there.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN **Potty Mouth**"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">The problem with resists is really that spells don't scale at the same rate as equipment does.&nbsp; For the most part, high level spells have the same resist rate as low level spells, while equipment resists go up tremendously as you level.&nbsp; What should happen is having higher resist mods added to higher level spells to compensate for the ease of acquiring resist equipment.&nbsp; You'd set the resist mods to account for a certain amount of resist gear less then what could be conceivably gained.&nbsp; Of course at some point you end up with the same imbalance, as casters have no way of making their spells more resistant, while their targets are continually increasing their resist gear.&nbsp; To offset this, I'd like to see focus effects for PvP resists available through the progression so that a well equipped caster is roughly equal to a well equipped target.&nbsp; This should address the concerns of many classes whose spells are highly resistant in PvP.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN **Potty Mouth**"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">For the several classes that are generally considered to be inferior in PvP I'd like to add some special abilities that compliment their current abilities and compensate for some of the weaknesses as well.&nbsp; For example, in testing right now I have Clerics with a silence spell that works only on players.&nbsp; Rogues have a combat ability that adds a snare proc to their ranged attacks.&nbsp; Warriors have a combat ability that adds a stun proc to their ranged weapons.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN **Potty Mouth**"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">These obviously aren't the end all be all of PvP balance, but it's a start.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN **Potty Mouth**"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">-Ryan</SPAN></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
