			I never expect to win a fight with someone that has me severely out geared and aa'd. I do, however, think that I should have a legitimate shot at defeating any class near my level and with similar stats. This is just not true. My monk regularly gets his ass handed to him by most hybrids, and almost always does by pure casters. Its a damn joke, plain and simple. The ways I resort to winning are not what I assume were intended. Oh.. a lake, woot! I carry a SFG for snare, pumice for cancel, invis potions, and a dot potion. This is not only inventory and weight burdening, but is expensive. Pumice is also WAY TOO SLOW. By the time I get one dot off me the caster has landed 2 more. Gotta get that DS off em, less I kill myself, and once again I get burned or dotted to all hell. If I manage to spam pumice they just run, and then hope I land one hit in 5 minutes of chasing. OMG, gottem to 20%, Gate... arghhhh! Next theres the ones that entitle me getting snared over and over. I thought to avoid this I should purchase resist gear. Now that even is worthless.<br><br>Something different needs to be done. I love pvp, and almost do not mind being on the losing side, as I enjoy the challenge, but damn, kick us a bone once in awhile.	
