		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I think you also need to consider the human issue in pvp.  What happens when you nerf "spells" and "abilities" is that you make gear that much important.  That's all well and good on a blue server, but on a pvp server, at least on my pvp server, the top guilds engage in mass pvp on raid forces that try to acquire the same gear they have.  The top-geared warrior on Tallon Zek is actually posting in the shadowknight.org forum complaining that shadowknights are the only class on our server that can kill him and therefore their abilities need to be nerfed for that reason.  His guild is the only guild with access to Plane of Time on our server, and they pride themselves in their ability to use their gear advantage in pvp to keep the rest of the server from even flagging for that zone.  Even if all classes were 100% balanced, it would do nothing to change high-end pvp because high-end pvp is more about the strength of your guild and the strength of your gear than it is about class abilities.<br><br>Callipygia	
		</td></tr>
