		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>The Beta Server lets you PK anyone you want within 4 or 5 levels. People make their own guilds or teams and just agree not to attack each other, so far its been SZ against everyone else because SZ seems to have more numbers the all others put together. I like this system as you can attack anyone you want basiacally, you dont need to be in a guild or anything.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As to the casual vs. hardcore, as one of the hardcore (7 level 65's with 200ish AA average), I would have no problem in not only limiting your attacks to people within 4 levels but once you are at 65 within 50 or so AA of yourself, I mean what is the point of just slaughtering someone.... no one should be forced into a battle they cannot possibly win. Actually level 62's with 30AA have no businees attacking level 65's with 200AA... </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would not favor a "day one" server as I have spent to much time on my toons to start again. But then again the SZ rules set of letting you attack anyone is no fair either. The Beta Server is very nice.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Again by far the best solution is a cross server instanced zone (or perment beta server) where you port into the bazzar from yur home server at will (say a new pok stone), if you die you go to your bind point on home server with full items, full mana, and all the buffs you had when you died and say a 3 mintues stun... Natually you could not trade items or plat or anything on the pvp server or instanced zone. So you can do yur PvE and Trades on yur home server and fight any time you want on the permanent beta server (which could be like just 3 or 4 zones - PoK, Nexus, Bazzar (no pvp) and whatever... </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just think Rallos could challenge&nbsp;a blue server &nbsp;on a Sunday and port in 200 people to take them on and the blue server would send 200 also.... heh. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The points board would only be for points goten on the permant beta server or&nbsp; instanced zone, not on yur home server. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is perfect as those who want to PvE and level can do so in peace and those who actually want to pvp can have mass battles or individual cross server matches.... </DIV>	
